## Gas Town Multi-Agent Orchestration

This project uses **Gas Town** (`gt`) for parallel multi-agent development on Linux.
Gas Town coordinates polecats (worker agents) through Mayor, Refinery, Witness, and Deacon.

**Gas Town HQ:** `~/gt/`
**Rig:** `~/gt/{{REPO_SLUG}}/`
**Polecat worktrees:** `~/gt/{{REPO_SLUG}}/polecats/<name>/{{REPO_SLUG}}/`

### Polecat Session Flow

```bash
gt prime          # Load role context + formula checklist (run first, every session)
gt mol status     # Check your hooked work
bd show <id>      # Full bead details
```

Work only inside your worktree (`~/gt/{{REPO_SLUG}}/polecats/<name>/{{REPO_SLUG}}/`).
Never edit files in the rig root — it has no `.git`, edits are lost.

**Session end (MANDATORY):**
```bash
git status && git add <files> && git commit -m "<id>: description" && git push
bd backup export-git
gt done           # Submit to Refinery merge queue — MANDATORY, replaces manual push
```

`gt done` verifies clean state, submits to Refinery, exits. Never push to main directly.

### OpenBrain Capture (Polecats)

The `mol-polecat-work` formula has a mandatory `capture-findings` gate step between
`commit-changes` and `pre-verify`. Polecats cannot submit to the merge queue without:

1. Calling `capture_thought("[TASK {{issue}}] [COMPLETED] ...")` with a structured summary
2. Updating bead notes: `bd update {{issue}} --notes "COMPLETED: <summary>"`

See formula step for exact format. OpenBrain MCP is pre-configured in opencode config.

### Communication Hygiene

- **Default:** `gt nudge <target> "msg"` — ephemeral, zero Dolt overhead
- **Escalate blockers:** `gt escalate "description" -s HIGH` — routes to Mayor
- **Persistent handoffs:** `gt mail send` — only when message must survive session death
- **Never mail "I'm done"** — `gt done` notifies Refinery automatically
- **Never close your bead** — Refinery closes it after merge

### Key Commands

```bash
gt prime              # Load full context + formula checklist
gt mol status         # Check hooked work
gt done               # Submit to merge queue
gt escalate "desc"    # Escalate blockers
gt mail inbox         # Check messages
gt nudge <target> "msg"  # Ephemeral message (prefer over mail)
```

### gstack Integration

Gas Town agents use gstack skills based on their role:
- **Mayor** uses `/plan-eng-review` before dispatching convoys
- **Refinery** gates merges with `/review` and `/cso` (security audit)
- **Flint (crew)** uses full sprint cycle for one-off tasks
- **Polecats do NOT use gstack** — they are execution units
